FBIS4-44044 "drweu122_o_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-122 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 CYPRUS British Prime Minister Replies to Kliridhis Letter British Prime Minister Replies to Kliridhis Letter NC2306195094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 1900 GMT 23 Jun 94 NC2306195094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] British Prime Minister John Major has conveyed his answer to President Glavkos Kliridhis' letter about negotiations at the UN Security Council regarding Butrus-Ghali's report. According to a reliable source, Major's letter is positive and ends the president's fears and concerns. The president sent personal letters to U.S. President Bill Clinton and Major expressing his intention to resign and declare early elections if the Security Council decided to continue talks on the confidence-building measures.
